Banana Pancakes
Difficulty: 2
Makes: 12 small pancakes

Ingredients
1 cup milk
1 egg
1Â¼ cup flour
2 tsp aluminum free baking powder 
Dash of lemon juice
1 banana

With an electric mixer, blend the milk, egg, flour, baking powder, and lemon juice together into a thick batter. Dice the banana and mix it evenly into the batter. Heat a skillet with oil, then spoon batter into the pan and fry, flipping to brown both sides evenly. Optional: top pancakes with syrup, honey, or homemade jam.
